    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix F1AP interface handling error in ESM dedicated bearer activation\n\n### Summary\nThe ESM receiver in the UE stack incorrectly rejected valid ACTIVATE DEDICATED EPS BEARER CONTEXT REQUEST messages when the Procedure Transaction Identity (PTI) was set to 0 (unassigned). This caused message loss and corruption in the F1AP interface processing path.\n\nThe issue occurred because the PTI validation logic did not properly account for the fact that dedicated bearer activation messages can have unassigned PTI values according to 3GPP TS 24.301 specification.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/ESM/SAP/esm_recv.c`: Modified PTI checking logic in `esm_recv_activate_dedicated_eps_bearer_context_request` to allow unassigned PTI values and fixed control flow structure.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Configure gNB with F1AP interface enabled\n2. Trigger dedicated EPS bearer context activation from the network with PTI=0\n3. Observe that the UE rejects the message with ESM_CAUSE_INVALID_PTI_VALUE\n4. The dedicated bearer activation procedure fails and the bearer context is not established\n\nThe fix ensures that valid dedicated bearer activation messages with PTI=0 are properly processed, resolving the F1AP interface handling error.\n"
}